# tools/size — a reusable B5 size-budget gate (the `size_limit` rule in defs.bzl). Any
# shipped artifact — kernel.wasm, the per-tier mcbox binaries, the flavor layer tars — wires
# its byte ceiling through one Starlark rule, so a regression fails CI instead of bloating
# silently. Pure Bazel: the rule's only shell is the `wc -c` byte count (which only the
# execution phase can do), wrapped in build_test. No target to declare here — consumers just
# `load("//bazel/tools/size:defs.bzl", "size_limit")`.
